[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Bedrock (Agents, Knowledge Bases, Guardrails, foundation model with strong tool-use, embedding model), Amazon OpenSearch Serverless, AWS HealthLake, AWS Lambda, AWS Step Functions, Amazon API Gateway, AWS WAF, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon S3, AWS KMS, AWS Secrets Manager, Amazon CloudWatch, AWS CloudTrail, Amazon EventBridge, Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose, AWS Glue, Amazon Athena, Amazon Pinpoint, Amazon Connect, Amazon QuickSight. Optionally Amazon SageMaker for custom gap-detection models. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **External Inputs** | EHR or FHIR-native chart-context (Patient, Condition, MedicationStatement, AllergyIntolerance, Encounter, ServiceRequest, Appointment, CarePlan, Goal, Observation) from each integrated EHR. Care-management platform integration. Scheduling system integration. Prior-authorization status feed. Referral-tracking system. Pharmacy-fill data feed. Home-health-agency status integration where applicable. Plan benefit data. Institutional content corpus (care-pathway templates, prior-authorization process documentation, social-services and transportation-resource directories, plan-specific benefit and policy data, care-team-contact directory, institutional care-management policies) curated and version-controlled by care-management leadership and clinical leadership. Validated translations for all patient-facing content. Care-navigation workforce capacity sized to patient population. 988 and 911 routing integration. State-specific consent and information-sharing variations. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | Per-Lambda least-privilege roles. Each integration-tool Lambda has narrowly-scoped read access to its specific source. Write access (e.g., booking an appointment, sending a portal message) requires explicit patient or care-navigator authorization and is gated by Step Functions workflows that record authorization. Resource-based policies pin invoking principals. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA and Compliance** | AWS BAA signed. Verify all services in scope are HIPAA-eligible at build time. The assistant operates across institutional boundaries with PHI of the most sensitive variety. Information-sharing agreements between integrated institutions are reviewed and operationalized. State-specific care-management regulations may apply. <!-- TODO: verify; care-management regulations vary by state and by program type (Medicare, Medicaid, commercial); specific compliance obligations vary --> |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | All stores encrypted at rest with customer-managed KMS keys. Sensitive categories (substance-use treatment data subject to 42 CFR Part 2, mental-health data subject to state-specific privacy enhancements) use separately-keyed encryption for blast-radius containment. S3 archives use Object Lock in compliance mode. TLS in transit for all AWS API calls and all integrations. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: tool Lambdas that call EHRs, care-management platforms, scheduling systems, prior-authorization feeds, pharmacy systems, and home-health agencies run in VPC with controlled egress. PrivateLink to vendor-hosted endpoints where supported; tightly-scoped NAT path with allow-list otherwise. VPC endpoints for DynamoDB, S3, KMS, Secrets Manager, CloudWatch Logs, EventBridge, Bedrock, OpenSearch Serverless, HealthLake, Step Functions, Pinpoint, Connect, and SageMaker (where used). The patient-facing edge is public; the back-office traffic is private. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled with data events on all sensitive S3 buckets and DynamoDB tables, Secrets Manager secrets, and customer-managed KMS keys. Bedrock and Bedrock Agents invocations logged. Lambda invocations logged. API Gateway access logs enabled. Step Functions execution logs enabled. Connect interactions logged. Audit retention sized to HIPAA's six-year minimum, state-specific care-management retention rules, and any litigation-hold obligations. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic patient profiles stratified by complexity tier, condition mix, age cohort, language, social-determinant context, and care-journey stage. Synthetic care plans, scheduled appointments, referrals, prior-authorization records, lab results, medication lists, and encounter histories. Synthetic care-management platform records. Validated institutional content corpus. Test EHR, care-management platform, scheduling system, prior-authorization feed, pharmacy, and home-health environments with synthetic data. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | At a mid-sized payer or health-system scale (50,000 active members across complexity tiers; high-complexity members average 8-15 conversational engagements per month plus continuous gap-detection and action-routing; moderate-complexity 2-5 engagements per month; low-complexity less than 1 per month; average 6-15 turns per engagement; average 3,000 tokens of prompt and 500 tokens of response per turn for the orchestration model plus tool-call overhead): Bedrock LLM invocations typically $5-12 per active member per month for a Sonnet-class orchestration model, totaling approximately $3M-7M per year. Bedrock Agents and Knowledge Bases plus OpenSearch Serverless typically $80,000-300,000 per year. Lambda, API Gateway, WAF, DynamoDB, S3, KMS, Secrets Manager, CloudWatch, CloudTrail, EventBridge, Kinesis Firehose, Glue, Athena, Step Functions total approximately $200,000-700,000 per year combined. AWS HealthLake typically $100,000-400,000 per year. Pinpoint typically $30,000-150,000 per year. Connect for navigator queue typically $200,000-800,000 per year. SageMaker (when used) typically $30,000-100,000 per year. Total AWS infrastructure typically $3.6M-9M per year at this scale (approximately $6-15 per active member per month). The care-navigation workforce cost is typically larger than the AWS infrastructure cost and is the dominant operational expense. <!-- TODO: replace with verified pricing once the implementing team validates against the AWS Pricing Calculator; specific costs depend on Bedrock model choice, conversation volume, source-integration count, FHIR-source choice, and channel mix --> |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock** | LLM for orchestration and conversational response generation; embedding model for institutional content corpus and conversation history |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Agents** | Tool orchestration: define coordination tools as action groups, manage the multi-step LLM-and-tool flow |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Knowledge Bases** | Managed RAG over (a) institutional content corpus (care pathways, prior-auth processes, social-services and transportation directories, benefits, care-team contacts), (b) longitudinal conversation history. Metadata-filtered retrieval (content type, condition, payer, geography, language, version) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon OpenSearch Serverless** | Vector and lexical retrieval index backing each Knowledge Base |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Bedrock Guardrails** | Content filtering for clinical-recommendation-attempted, care-plan-change-attempted, medication-adjustment-attempted, payer-dispute-conclusion-attempted, crisis-handling-attempted |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Chat handler; input/output screening; identity-and-context loading; consolidation pipeline; gap-detection engine; action-routing handler; care-management-reporting pipeline; tool implementations |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Step Functions** | Multi-step action workflows (e.g., draft-and-route a prior-authorization appeal, draft-and-route a portal message, schedule-and-confirm an appointment proposal) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon API Gateway** | Public-facing chat endpoint for web, app, SMS, and voice channels |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS WAF** | Rate limiting, bot detection, common attack patterns |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | patient-longitudinal-store, consolidated-view-store, gap-inventory-store, action-log-store, conversation-state, conversation-metadata, tool-call-ledger, coordination-decision-record-journal, consent-record |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Institutional content corpus, conversation archive, decision-record journal, outcome-correlation data |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS HealthLake** | FHIR-native consolidation layer across multiple source EHRs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Customer-managed encryption keys per data class with separate keys for sensitive categories |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Secrets Manager** | Credentials for EHRs, care-management platforms, scheduling systems, prior-authorization feeds, pharmacy systems, home-health agencies, and benefits systems |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon CloudWatch** | Operational metrics (engagement rate, gap-detection sensitivity, action-completion rate, navigator-productivity gain, per-cohort outcome trajectories); alarms |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS CloudTrail** | API-level audit logging |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon EventBridge** | Assistant-event bus and source-event bus (appointment_scheduled, appointment_canceled, prior_auth_decision_returned, referral_status_changed, lab_result_available, medication_filled, encounter_completed, gap_detected, action_routed, action_completed, etc.) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Pinpoint** | Patient-facing notifications and reminders (push, SMS) with delivery-status tracking |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Connect** | Warm-handoff queue for the care-navigation workforce (chat and voice) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose** | Streaming audit and telemetry delivery |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Glue Data Catalog + Amazon Athena** | SQL access to audit, decision-record, and telemetry data |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SageMaker (where used)** | Hosted custom gap-detection-model inference |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon QuickSight** | Operational and outcome dashboards |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
